04:07.664 --> 04:08.832
- Were those texts
that were between

04:08.832 --> 04:10.542
you and a student?

04:10.542 --> 04:11.585
- Yes, they were.

04:11.585 --> 04:14.504
♪ ♪

04:14.504 --> 04:17.549
I think that what the main
problem they had with it

04:17.549 --> 04:19.593
is they don't understand
the way

04:19.593 --> 04:21.261
that the Spanish language
works.

04:21.261 --> 04:24.139
There is two different ways
to say, you know--

04:24.139 --> 04:27.768
you know, "Love you,
have a great day, fantastic."

04:27.768 --> 04:30.979
You know, there's te quiero,
which is basically used

04:30.979 --> 04:33.273
in front of family
and friends.

04:33.273 --> 04:36.526
You know, I say that
to all my former students.

04:36.526 --> 04:38.320
Te quiero.
And there's the te amo,

04:38.320 --> 04:43.366
which is--that's a bit serious,
and you don't want to do that,

04:43.366 --> 04:46.161
um, in any way, shape, or form.

04:46.161 --> 04:49.956
So for me, all those texts
that I had--that I'd sent

04:49.956 --> 04:52.501
this particular student,

04:52.501 --> 04:54.336
were basically support.

04:54.336 --> 04:55.754
"Hey, nice hair.

04:55.754 --> 04:58.507
Love the change of hair.
Fantastic."

04:58.507 --> 05:01.343
In retrospect, yeah, probably
shouldn't have sent them.

05:01.343 --> 05:03.470
But at the same time,
any kind of support

05:03.470 --> 05:06.056
I would've be able
to give them,

05:06.056 --> 05:07.516
I don't regret that.

05:07.516 --> 05:09.726
♪ ♪

05:09.726 --> 05:12.145
- If my daughter was getting
those text messages

05:12.145 --> 05:14.231
from a teacher,

05:14.231 --> 05:16.983
I would be at the school
that same day.

05:16.983 --> 05:18.109
Period.

05:18.109 --> 05:19.861
End of story.

05:19.861 --> 05:21.863
Yeah, no, I don't believe him.

05:21.863 --> 05:23.698
I don't believe him.

05:23.698 --> 05:25.492
I can't believe him.

05:25.492 --> 05:29.746
The story with Tom
has this greater kind of arc

05:29.746 --> 05:33.458
of not understanding
where the line is

05:33.458 --> 05:36.294
and kind of placing the blame
