33:05.609 --> 33:07.485
to testify.

33:07.485 --> 33:11.364
Like, it's on me
to carry that through.

33:11.364 --> 33:13.742
And it's a lot.

33:13.742 --> 33:16.661
[melancholic piano music]

33:16.661 --> 33:22.083
♪ ♪

33:22.083 --> 33:23.126
- Good morning, Judge.
Jessie Freeman

33:23.126 --> 33:24.544
on behalf of the state.

33:24.544 --> 33:25.879
- We have sounding on Thursday.

33:25.879 --> 33:26.838
You wanna go ahead
and let me know

33:26.838 --> 33:28.423
what the status is now?

33:28.423 --> 33:30.300
- Yes, Your Honor.
State's ready.

33:30.300 --> 33:33.887
And I do have Heaven,
the victim on the case.

33:33.887 --> 33:35.931
She is present on the Zoom
as well as my trial partner.

33:35.931 --> 33:37.474
That date does work.

33:37.474 --> 33:39.768
We were looking forward
to going to trial now.

33:39.768 --> 33:41.061
- Defense is ready as well.

33:41.061 --> 33:42.896
That said, there are issues

33:42.896 --> 33:46.316
with the practicality
of it going on March 14th.

33:46.316 --> 33:53.240
♪ ♪

33:55.909 --> 33:58.036
- Okay, good morning.

33:58.036 --> 34:00.288
- Good morning.
- Morning.

34:00.288 --> 34:03.250
- Judge, state's ready
to begin trial on 4/25.

34:03.250 --> 34:05.210
The lead detective,
Detective Web,

34:05.210 --> 34:10.632
is in a--about a month-long
training in Alabama.

34:10.632 --> 34:13.009
What I discussed
with Mr. Horenstein

34:13.009 --> 34:16.179
was possibly picking a jury
the week of 4/25

34:16.179 --> 34:19.099
and then starting testimony
on the week of 5/2

34:19.099 --> 34:21.726
or in the alternative,
having Detective Web testify

34:21.726 --> 34:24.854
via Zoom at the trial
during the week of 4/25.

34:24.854 --> 34:27.357
- Defense,
what's your preference?

34:27.357 --> 34:28.858
- Your Honor,
I'll object to both.

34:28.858 --> 34:30.610
- Okay.

34:30.610 --> 34:32.445
- Having the detective--
the lead detective on the case

34:32.445 --> 34:34.447
via Zoom is not going to work.

34:34.447 --> 34:35.448
- I'm gonna be honest with you.

34:35.448 --> 34:38.660
We start Monday.

34:38.660 --> 34:41.079
I don't know that we'd be able
to pick a jury in a day.

34:41.079 --> 34:43.081
- Okay.
- Tuesday I have to finish

34:43.081 --> 34:46.126
no later than 4:00.
- Okay.

34:46.126 --> 34:48.295
- We're all gonna make
our best efforts,

34:48.295 --> 34:50.380
but I can't promise you
when it's gonna be done.

34:50.380 --> 34:53.466
- The State chose
to wait six years

34:53.466 --> 34:54.926
to decide
that they wanted the trial

34:54.926 --> 34:56.386
and waited until--
- Right.

34:56.386 --> 34:57.887
I understand
what you're saying.

34:57.887 --> 34:59.347
You know, it's last-minute.

34:59.347 --> 35:02.309
I 100% agree,
but they're still timely,

35:02.309 --> 35:04.561
so I don't think that I should
impose the most

35:04.561 --> 35:07.230
onerous sanction
and have her stricken.

35:07.230 --> 35:12.652
♪ ♪

35:14.321 --> 35:17.282
[soft tense music]

35:17.282 --> 35:18.867
♪ ♪

35:18.867 --> 35:20.702
If we're not gonna be in trial,

35:20.702 --> 35:23.997
I already have another trial
set second, waiting to go.

35:23.997 --> 35:25.540
[laughs]
- Yeah.

35:25.540 --> 35:28.752
- Thank you, Mr. Meyers and...

35:28.752 --> 35:32.964
the rest of the people
that are on the Zoom.

35:32.964 --> 35:39.971
♪ ♪

35:39.971 --> 35:42.390
- It's just hard.
It's just really hard

35:42.390 --> 35:44.351
on my emotions and...

35:44.351 --> 35:47.354
[cries]

35:47.354 --> 35:54.361
♪ ♪

35:56.863 --> 35:59.115
That's, like, the reality
of being victim.

35:59.115 --> 36:01.826
It's...

36:01.826 --> 36:05.372
extensive, unreasonable delays,

36:05.372 --> 36:08.792
lots of back and forth.

36:08.792 --> 36:10.710
Does waiting six years
for trial,

36:10.710 --> 36:12.629
is that "speedy"?

36:12.629 --> 36:19.552
♪ ♪

36:36.444 --> 36:40.031
- I think too often we...

36:40.031 --> 36:44.035
we put pressure on the victims
to explain to us

36:44.035 --> 36:46.496
their trauma, their experience

36:46.496 --> 36:52.419
to teach us and educate us
about what they've gone through

36:52.419 --> 36:55.004
so that we have
a better understanding of it.

36:55.004 --> 36:59.092
And that's putting too much
of the onus on the victims

36:59.092 --> 37:02.595
to take responsibility
for what was, in fact,

37:02.595 --> 37:06.433
done to them by somebody else.

37:08.852 --> 37:11.521
We don't spend enough time
pointing the finger

37:11.521 --> 37:13.940
at the perpetrator
of the crime.

37:13.940 --> 37:15.191
We need to talk about

37:15.191 --> 37:17.902
how the perpetrators
need to change,

37:17.902 --> 37:22.449
not how we need
to avoid being victimized.

37:26.286 --> 37:29.622
[moody music]

37:29.622 --> 37:32.584
♪ ♪

37:32.584 --> 37:35.170
You know,
people keep asking me

37:35.170 --> 37:40.508
if I feel like
I've found resolution

37:40.508 --> 37:43.845
or if I feel healed in any way.

37:44.929 --> 37:48.641
And I look
at the different ways

37:48.641 --> 37:52.854
that Heaven and Alisson and I

37:52.854 --> 37:56.232
have all processed
through our trauma.

37:56.232 --> 37:58.401
And for Alisson,

37:58.401 --> 38:04.032
she sat in a room and spent
time with her journals

38:04.032 --> 38:06.451
and then she wrote a memoir.

38:06.451 --> 38:12.999
And for Heaven, she decided
that the legal system

38:12.999 --> 38:15.543
was the way that she was going
to process through her trauma.

38:15.543 --> 38:18.421
♪ ♪

38:18.421 --> 38:21.257
For me, I decided
to make a documentary

38:21.257 --> 38:23.802
because that was the way
that I processed

38:23.802 --> 38:26.012
through my pain,
and I'm a filmmaker,

38:26.012 --> 38:28.848
and so that's how I wanted
to process my trauma.

38:28.848 --> 38:33.520
♪ ♪

38:33.520 --> 38:39.067
I think in looking at our three
very different experiences,

38:39.067 --> 38:41.861
what I've realized is,

38:41.861 --> 38:46.115
at the end of that road...

38:46.115 --> 38:48.701
in a way,
there is no resolution

38:48.701 --> 38:54.749
because there is no way to tie
this experience up in a bow

38:54.749 --> 38:58.670
and, you know, put it away
on a shelf.

38:58.670 --> 38:59.963
[Daniel Farrant's
"Who's Gonna Fix It"]

38:59.963 --> 39:01.381
- ♪ Don't you know
that you gotta ♪

39:01.381 --> 39:03.967
♪ Take some of the blame ♪

39:05.927 --> 39:09.556
♪ You said those unkind words
'cause you think it's a game ♪

39:09.556 --> 39:11.057
♪ Well, it's not ♪

39:11.057 --> 39:15.645
♪ And it's got real serious ♪

39:15.645 --> 39:16.938
♪ Who's gonna fix it? ♪

39:16.938 --> 39:18.106
♪ Time to give it up ♪

39:18.106 --> 39:19.649
♪ Look around, get found ♪

39:19.649 --> 39:21.901
♪ But it don't
make a new sound ♪

39:21.901 --> 39:24.612
♪ No joke 'cause it's broke ♪

39:24.612 --> 39:27.448
♪ Who's gonna fix it? ♪

39:27.448 --> 39:29.784
♪ Who's gonna
fix it? ♪

39:29.784 --> 39:36.708
♪ ♪

39:52.932 --> 39:56.227
- This is what we've been
living with forever,

39:56.227 --> 39:59.856
so it would have
to take something enormous

39:59.856 --> 40:01.649
to change here.

40:01.649 --> 40:06.321
When you think about teaching
children about consent,

40:06.321 --> 40:08.990
that's actually a huge thing,

40:08.990 --> 40:11.117
but it's something small
that we can do

40:11.117 --> 40:13.036
in our everyday lives

40:13.036 --> 40:16.247
that is radically different
from my experience.

40:16.247 --> 40:18.625
♪ ♪

40:18.625 --> 40:20.919
- I think
it is incredibly important

40:20.919 --> 40:24.380
for parents, for teachers,
for administrators,

40:24.380 --> 40:28.384
for adults to understand
how this happens,

40:28.384 --> 40:30.428
to be able to identify
the stages of grooming

40:30.428 --> 40:34.098
and to feel confident
and empowered

40:34.098 --> 40:36.017
to say something.

40:38.770 --> 40:42.273
- I don't really know
what's next after this either,

40:42.273 --> 40:44.984
but I don't feel like
I'm done yet.

40:44.984 --> 40:47.737
It's not really what I want
to do with my life,

40:47.737 --> 40:48.863
but...

40:50.657 --> 40:53.117
To feel fulfilled
within myself,

40:53.117 --> 40:56.120
like, I can't put it down.

40:56.120 --> 40:59.207
I feel like there's still
so much more to do.

40:59.207 --> 41:01.668
♪ ♪

41:01.668 --> 41:04.337
- Hopefully,
by telling your story,

41:04.337 --> 41:06.547
you can inspire other girls,

41:06.547 --> 41:08.132
you can raise awareness,

41:08.132 --> 41:10.134
you can create a vocabulary.

41:10.134 --> 41:12.720
You might even be able
to change some laws.

41:12.720 --> 41:14.764
No matter how you come forward,

41:14.764 --> 41:20.019
it's a difficult, painful,
ugly, messy process.

41:20.019 --> 41:23.898
It...it stays with you
for your whole life.

41:23.898 --> 41:30.822
